  "body": "## Preamble\r\n\r\n    EIP: <to be assigned>\r\n    Title: Proposal for automatic ETH payments\r\n    Author: Joao Nunes, joao3001@hotmail.com\r\n    Type: Standard Track\r\n    Category (*only required for Standard Track): Core\r\n    Status: Draft\r\n    Created: 2017-07-30\r\n\r\n\r\n## Simple Summary\r\nAutomatic payments in ETH without breaking any security\r\n\r\n## Abstract\r\nMy proposal is a new feature for ETH to support automatic payments without breaking any security\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nA user wants to use a service that needs a credit card. The service charges him every time he uses the service.\r\n\r\nExample: Apple iTunes.\r\nEvery time the user buys an app, Apple will charge the user's card.\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\nCreate a pay out address associated with my own account.\r\n\r\nRules\r\n\r\n1) The payout address is linked to my own wallet\r\n2) The payout can only be charged by only one merchant\r\n3) There is a daily and monthly withdraw limit\r\n4) There is a way to query if the payout address has enough funds to make the purchase\r\n5) The wallet address cannot be known using only the payout address\r\n\r\n## Rationale\r\n1) it can only get coins from my own address\r\n2) only one address can receive transfers from this payout address.\r\n3) Added security\r\n4) This will trigger a query to the wallet\r\n5) Added security\r\n\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\nYES\r\n\r\n## Test Cases\r\nNA\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\nNA\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/).\r\n",
