    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "A generalization of this proposal, I believe, would be the ability to give a contract rights to _pull_ funds from an account.  Something like approval.  One could then author the contract to have any ruleset it wants (including the rules proposed here).\r\n\r\nOne can already achieve this by transferring ETH into a wallet with these rules, but the disadvantage is that the user has to set-aside funds into the second contract, meaning they will no longer show up as part of the account holder's total balance.  If one has a lot of recurring subscriptions, then you quickly end up with a bunch of miscellaneous accounts.\r\n\r\nAnother option would be to create a standard wallet interface that supports constrained subscriptions.  This would be similar to ERC20 in that it would be an API standard that all wallets could implement that would allow functions like, \"setup recurring subscription\" and \"setup withdraw allowance\".  Then anyone that uses a compatible wallet would be able to use such services,\r\n\r\nI think all of these solutions become more palatable once accounts can have contract code associated with them (I don't remember the EIP).",
